## Phase 1 — Wazuh OVA Import and Network Setup

### Initial Observations

The Wazuh OVA was imported into VirtualBox successfully. On first boot the VM appeared to freeze at a console screen with no desktop environment. This was expected behavior — the Wazuh OVA is a server appliance and has no GUI. Boot completion is confirmed by seeing the login prompt on the console.

Boot logs confirmed:
- VBoxService started successfully
- eth0 became ready
- eth1 became ready

The appliance detected two interfaces: eth0 and eth1.

### VirtualBox Resource Reduction

The OVA imports with maximum default resources which caused the host laptop to become unresponsive when running alongside other VMs.

| Setting | OVA Default | Reduced To |
|---------|------------|------------|
| RAM | 8192 MB | 4096 MB |
| CPUs | 4 | 2 |
| Boot Order | Optical first | Hard Disk first |

### Network Adapter Configuration

The Wazuh OVA has two adapters. Adapter 1 was disabled (no NAT needed — internet routes through OPNsense). Adapter 2 was set to Internal Network (intnet) to connect to the lab network.

The active interface inside the VM mapped to eth0 with altname enp0s8, confirming it corresponds to VirtualBox Adapter 2.

