## Phase 2 — Static IP Configuration

The network config file referenced in older tutorials (/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-eth0) existed but contained leftover DHCP settings from the OVA import process.

### Original File (Problematic)

```
DEVICE=eth0
BOOTPROTO=none
ONBOOT=yes
TYPE=Ethernet
USERCTL=yes
PEERDNS=yes
DHCPV6C=yes
DHCPV6C_OPTIONSS=-nw
PERSISTENT_DHCLIENT=yes
RES_OPTIONS="timeout:2 attempts:5"
```

Problems: Missing IPADDR, NETMASK, GATEWAY, DNS1. Contained leftover DHCP-related lines.

### Corrected File

```
DEVICE=eth0
BOOTPROTO=none
ONBOOT=yes
TYPE=Ethernet
NM_CONTROLLED=no
NAME=eth0
IPADDR=10.200.200.5
NETMASK=255.255.255.0
GATEWAY=10.200.200.254
DNS1=8.8.8.8
```

Applied with:
```bash
sudo systemctl restart network
```

Static IP confirmed:
```bash
ip addr show eth0
# inet 10.200.200.5/24
```

