## Phase 4 — Agent Installation

### Windows 10 Agent

Installed via PowerShell:
```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/windows/wazuh-agent-4.14.5-1.msi -OutFile $env:tmp\wazuh-agent; msiexec.exe /i $env:tmp\wazuh-agent /q WAZUH_MANAGER='10.200.200.5'
```

Started the agent service:
```powershell
NET START WazuhSvc
```

### Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS Agent

Ubuntu Server was deployed as a separate VM for agent testing.

**VirtualBox settings:**
| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| RAM | 2048 MB |
| CPUs | 1 |
| Adapter 1 | Internal Network — intnet |

**Static IP via Netplan (/etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml):**
```yaml
network:
  version: 2
  ethernets:
    enp0s8:
      dhcp4: false
      addresses:
        - 10.200.200.21/24
      routes:
        - to: default
          via: 10.200.200.254
      nameservers:
        addresses: [10.200.200.254, 8.8.8.8]
```

Applied with:
```bash
sudo netplan apply
```

**SSH access from Windows:**
```powershell
ssh ubuntu@10.200.200.21
```

Note: openssh-server was not installed by default. Installed manually:
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openssh-server -y
sudo systemctl enable ssh
sudo systemctl start ssh
```

Wazuh agent installed via Wazuh dashboard deployment instructions.

