## Key Lessons

- The Wazuh OVA is a headless server appliance — no desktop GUI is expected or needed
- Always reduce OVA default resources before running alongside other lab VMs
- OPNsense must always be the first VM started — it is the gateway for every other VM
- Cleaning up previous episode configurations before starting a new lab phase prevents silent conflicts
- A single disabled OPNsense LAN firewall rule silently breaks internet access for all clients
- Ping asymmetry between Linux and Windows hosts is normal due to Windows Firewall ICMP rules — use HTTPS or TCP port tests for real connectivity validation
- Ubuntu Server uses Netplan for network configuration, not the legacy ifcfg scripts used by the Wazuh OVA
- SSH is not always pre-installed on Ubuntu Server — install openssh-server manually if needed
